{{future sport|image=AmericanFootball current event.svg}} {{NCAATeamFootballSeason |Year=2009 |Team=Army Black Knights |Image=USMA-BlackKnights-Logo.svg |ImageSize=185 |Conference=NCAA Division I FBS independent schools |ShortConference=Independent |CoachRank= |APRank= |BCSRank= |Record= 0&ndash;0 |ConfRecord= 0&ndash;0 |HeadCoach=[[Rich Ellerson]] |OffCoach= Gene McKeehan/Ian Shields |DefCoach= Payam Saadat/Chris Smeland |OScheme= |StadiumArena=[[Michie Stadium]] |Champion= |BowlTourney= |BowlTourneyResult= |ConfChamp= |ConfChampResult= }} {{2009 Independent football standings}} The '''2009 Army Black Knights football team''' will represent the [[United States Military Academy]] (USMA or "West Point") in [[National Collegiate Athletic Association]] (NCAA) [[Division I]] [[Division I#Football Bowl Subdivision|Football Bowl Subdivision]] (FBS) [[college football]] during the [[2009 NCAA Division I FBS football season|2009 season]]. Army will compete as an Indepedent, with no conference affiliation.
Army will be led by former Cal Poly head coach Rich Ellerson, the third winningest coach at that school.
