Grime Daily was built from the heart of the UK grime and rap music scene, for the UK  music scene!  With the likes of World Star Hip Hop and Smack tube on the internet there was definitely a need for UK music from the underground to have a platform where people could actually see the artists.  Music visuals are very important as people want to be able to see the artists in the flesh to get a sense of the person, whether they are really like their music suggests, what kind of person they are? The UK music scene didn’t have any such platform!

Grime daily is trying to bring the UK music scene to a wider audience and wants to make sure UK grime music and underground UK music in general gets the recognition that it deserves. UK grime music and all of the other underground UK music’s such as  hip hop, UK funky, Drum and bass, Bassline, Dub step and anything else in the so called ‘UK urban scene’ gets out there and in peoples faces as there is some very good music out there to be heard.

